<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1314,1987]" box="[199,1282,1386,1411]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1386,1411]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named after the Latin for “rough”, alluding to the granular surfaces of the carapace.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="135" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1314,1987]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,547,1422,1447]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Diagnosis of female 
<typeStatus box="[437,542,1422,1447]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Carapace subquadrate, wider than long, width 
<number box="[1075,1110,1422,1447]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times length, dorsal surfaces almost entirely covered with small tubercles, regions indistinct (
<figureCitation box="[878,947,1458,1483]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[932,947,1459,1483]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A); anterolateral margin arcuate, lined with small rounded granules; posterolateral margin with slight protuberance; posterolateral corner with angled prominence over base of posterior pereopods (
<figureCitation box="[675,742,1530,1555]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[728,742,1531,1555]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A); front deflexed (
<figureCitation box="[961,1029,1530,1555]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[1014,1029,1531,1555]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B); orbit distinct, eye small, slightly movable, cornea pigmented (
<figureCitation box="[489,560,1566,1591]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[545,560,1567,1591]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B); suborbital, overall pterygostomial, and subhepatic regions covered with scattered granules (
<figureCitation box="[375,446,1602,1627]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[431,446,1603,1626]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C); pterygostomial region with oblique striae, dense setae under striae adjacent to Milne Edwards opening (
<figureCitation box="[435,502,1638,1663]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[487,502,1639,1662]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
B, C); third maxillipeds broad, completely covering buccal cavity; outer surfaces of ischium, merus covered with numerous small granules; ischium subequal in length to merus, with gently rounded mesial margin (
<figureCitation box="[332,411,1710,1735]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. A – F" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1246,1268]" captionTargetBox="[163,1419,187,1223]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,175,1233]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. A – F, Hexapinus latipes (De Haan, 1835), male (20.9 × 12.5 mm) (SMF ZMG 160 a), Ambon, Indonesia; G, H, Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, ventral view of left G 1; B, dorsal view of left G 1; C, ventral view of distal part of left G 1; D, dorsal view of distal part of left G 1 (setae not drawn); E, left G 2 (ventral view); F, distal half of left G 2 (dorsal view); G, left third maxilliped; H, female abdomen. Scales: A, B, E, G, H = 1.0 mm; C, D, F = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241821/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Figs. 
<number box="[398,411,1710,1735]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
G, 
<number box="[446,461,1711,1735]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
C); chelipeds approximately symmetrical, slightly gaping when fingers closed; outer surfaces granulated (
<figureCitation box="[387,456,1746,1771]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[442,456,1747,1771]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B); P 
<number box="[553,566,1747,1771]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="2.0">2</number>
–P 
<number box="[596,610,1747,1771]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="4.0">4</number>
short, stout, outer surfaces with numerous distinct small granules, short setae, P 
<number box="[237,250,1783,1807]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="3.0">3</number>
stoutest, longest, longitudinal groove on merus barely visible (
<figureCitation box="[952,1029,1782,1807]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Figs. 
<number box="[1015,1029,1783,1807]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
A); thoracic sternum broad (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1410,1782,1807]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[1396,1410,1783,1807]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
C, D), sternites 1, 2 fused, separated from sternite 
<number box="[692,706,1819,1843]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="3.0">3</number>
by distinct ridge; sternite 
<number box="[1006,1020,1819,1843]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="3.0">3</number>
separated from sternite 
<number box="[1295,1309,1819,1843]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="4.0">4</number>
by distinct ridge; sternites 
<number box="[329,371,1855,1879]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="5.5" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="4.0">4–7</number>
distinct, separated by distinct sutures; sternite 
<number box="[916,930,1855,1879]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="8.0">8</number>
not visible; vulvae large, without opercular cover, on anterior half on sternite 
<number box="[551,567,1890,1915]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="6.0">6</number>
, opening lunate (
<figureCitation box="[771,842,1890,1915]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[189,1396,193,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[189,1397,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 7. Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, overall habitus; B, frontal view of cephalothorax and chelae; C, thoracic sternum and abdomen; D, sternoabdominal cavity and vulvae (v)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241822/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Fig. 
<number box="[827,842,1891,1915]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
</figureCitation>
D); abdomen subovate, with 
<number box="[1180,1194,1890,1915]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="6.0">6</number>
free somites, telson; somite 
<number box="[232,246,1926,1951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="6.0">6</number>
longest, trapezoidal, subequal in length to telson, telson subtriangular with rounded tip (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1315,1926,1951]" captionStart="FIGURE 6. A – F" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1246,1268]" captionTargetBox="[163,1419,187,1223]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1435,175,1233]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 6. A – F, Hexapinus latipes (De Haan, 1835), male (20.9 × 12.5 mm) (SMF ZMG 160 a), Ambon, Indonesia; G, H, Mariaplax aspera n. sp., holotype female (6.4 × 4.4 mm) (MZB), Lombok, Indonesia. A, ventral view of left G 1; B, dorsal view of left G 1; C, ventral view of distal part of left G 1; D, dorsal view of distal part of left G 1 (setae not drawn); E, left G 2 (ventral view); F, distal half of left G 2 (dorsal view); G, left third maxilliped; H, female abdomen. Scales: A, B, E, G, H = 1.0 mm; C, D, F = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/241821/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
Figs. 
<number box="[1301,1315,1926,1951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
H, 
<number box="[1349,1364,1927,1951]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="7.0">7</number>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1314,1987]" box="[199,1240,1962,1987]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,266,1962,1987]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135">Color</emphasis>
. Carapace light brown, mottled red and dark brown; chelipeds and P 
<number box="[1037,1051,1963,1987]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="2.0">2</number>
−P 
<number box="[1082,1096,1963,1987]" pageId="10" pageNumber="135" value="4.0">4</number>
light brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
